Here you will wake up in your own peaceful room, with a view of San Fra

The space
Casa de Paz (House of Peace) is like staying with family! If you want to experience San Francisco
like a local...instead of feeling like a tourist, this is the place for you.
Here you will wake up in your own peaceful room, with a view of San Francisco & the smell of fresh coffee brewing downstairs!

You may also enjoy the following amenities:
Use of kitchen
Internet/cable
Laundry Facilities
Beautiful Hiking right outside the back door! (Also, walking distance from the 49er stadium if you're a football fan!)
Less than 1 &1/2 blocks from public transportation (T-line light rail)
Minutes away from all main freeways, provides a quick commute

description:
The Donatello is a timeshare/hotel which is one of the top hotels in San Francisco. Just show up and check in like any other hotel, no arranging to get keys necessary.

- 1 KING BED and 1 QUEEN SLEEPER SOFA
- Parking: $32 per night

The space
DESCRIPTION
With 400 square feet of space and 10 foot ceilings, these rooms are some of the largest in the San Francisco area. Rooms are elegant and provide many of the luxuries of home including wet-bar and sink, compact refrigerator and microwave, sofa sleeper, cd player and in-room safe. All rooms have one KING BED and one QUEEN SLEEPER SOFA and sleep maximum of 4 people. No rollaways are available.

name: The Donatello Hotel (Union Square)
description:
Stay one block from Union Square in a roomy, newly renovated hotel room at one of the top timeshare hotels in San Francisco. There are various room-types available, so please specify your needs when requesting a reservation.

The space
Located in the heart of San Francisco's fashionable shopping and theater district near numerous attractions, the Donatello Hotel boasts a charming Italian atmosphere, superior amenities and attentive staff. Restaurants, shopping, nightclubs are all steps away. One block to Union Square, cable cars and world famous landmarks. Fisherman's Wharf and Pier 39 is a cable car ride away.

With 400 square feet of space and 10-foot ceilings, these rooms are some of the largest in the San Francisco area. When booking, please indicate your room requirements and preferences. Available room types: king room, king room with (queen) sofa sleeper, ADA-compliant King room, or a room with two double beds.

name: Waterfront 2 Bdr Apt -Fishermans Wharf - Bay Views
description:
Spacious 2-bedroom Penthouse Suite (sleeps 6)
Some highlights are:
*2 Bedroom Apartment unit is on the top floor (the 4th floor- completely private) of a motel in the heart of Fisherman's Wharf San Francisco.
* Large living room, dining table, kitchen, wraparound deck with views of the SF bay
*In-unit washer & dryer
*Great location (5-minute walk) to Fisherman's Wharf's finest landmarks including: Pier 39, Alcatraz, Cable Cars, and Lombard-Crooked Street
* Free parking for 1 vehicle included

The space
Welcome to our 2 Bedroom Penthouse Suite located in Fishermanâ€™s Wharf San Francisco!

Our penthouse provides beautiful views of San Francisco and the world-famous Bay from our private wrap-around 280-degree balcony. The penthouse is located in a hotel in Fishermanâ€™s Wharf (Wharf Inn). All major attraction including Pier 39, Ghirardelli Square, Alcatraz, Cable Cars are less than a 10-minute walk.
The unit can sleep 6 an
neighborhood_overview:
Many of San Francisco most visited area's (Alcatraz, Pier 39, Ghirardelli Square) are a stones throw away.

We are a quick muni ( Street car) ride away from famous SF Giants Ball Park and Home of the Golden State Warriors Chase Center.

San Francisco's iconic bread factory Boudin is literally right around the corner.

San Francisco's most prominent Open Top Sightseeing Bus Tour (Big Bus ) begins from across the Street.

World famous Madam Tussauds and the Ripley Believe it Or Not museums are 1 block away.

The area has more than 100+ restaurants to choose from, from Fine Dining to Casual and Fast Food. There is an option for every palate type.
host_about:
Living the dream- enjoy travelling with my husband and hosting guests in this beautiful city.
Best place to experience Fisherman's Wharf- Standing at Pier 39 listening to the sea lions!

name: Downtown SF Timeshare/Hotel Studio
description:
The Donatello is a timeshare/hotel which is one of the top hotels in San Francisco. Just show up and check in like any other hotel, no arranging to get keys necessary.

- 1 KING BED and 1 QUEEN SLEEPER SOFA
- Parking: $32 per night

The space
DESCRIPTION
With 400 square feet of space and 10 foot ceilings, these rooms are some of the largest in the San Francisco area. Rooms are elegant and provide many of the luxuries of home including wet-bar and sink, compact refrigerator and microwave, sofa sleeper, cd player and in-room safe. All rooms have one KING BED and one QUEEN SLEEPER SOFA and sleep maximum of 4 people. No rollaways are available.

Services & Amenities:
Spacious studio accommodations
24-hour front desk
Concierge services
Intimate Italian dining at Zingari Ristorante
Indoor valet parking ($32 per night, unlimited in and out privileges)
Meeting facilities
Dry cleaning services (fee)
Roo

From arranging dinner reservations or sailing excursions to booking tickets for theatrical, cultural, or sporting events, Our personalized service allows you convenient access to all that San Francisco has to offer.

Full private apartment.

name: The Donatello Hotel one block from Union Square
description:
The Donatello is located precisely one block from Union Square, in the heart of San Francisco's fabulous shopping, top-rated theater, and international dining district. You're only minutes by cab or cable car from the city's other legendary attractions. To make sure you make the most of it all, you only need to ask at the Concierge desk in the top-floor lounge.

The space
The resort offers a fitness center, sauna and indoor hot tub as well as the renowned Zingari Italian restaurant. At day's end, you'll retire to a unit that boasts soaring 10-foot ceilings and oversized windows. The spacious, exquisitely decorated and elegant accommodations are your home away from home. After a day of exploring the city or visiting the nearby wineries of Napa or Sonoma Valley, cap off the evening in the top floor lounge or view the city's lights from the adjoining rooftop terrace.

Resort Features
ATM
Bar
Business Center
Fitness Center
Concierge

neighborhood_overview:
Russian Hill is directly to the north (and slightly downhill) from Nob Hill, to the south (uphill) from Fisherman's Wharf, and to the west of the North Beach neighborhood. The Hill is bordered on its west side by parts of the neighborhoods of Cow Hollow and the Marina District.

At the northern foot of the hill is Ghirardelli Square, which sits on the waterfront of the San Francisco Bay, Aquatic Park, and Fisherman's Wharf, a popular tourist area. A trip down the winding turns of Lombard Street and across Columbus Avenue to the east leads to the neighborhood of North Beach. Down the hill to the west, past Van Ness Avenue, are Cow Hollow and the Marina districts.

name: Shell Vacation Club/ San Fran
description:
Ideally located on the edge of legendary Fisherman's Wharf, the Suites at Fisherman's Wharf offers the excitement and fun of San Francisco right outside. The famous Hyde Street Cable Car stops at the front doorstep and leads to Chinatown, Nob Hill, and Union Square. Steps away from the resort is the Cannery, Aquatic Park, Ghirardelli Square and Pier 39.

The space
Each of the resort's fully furnished, spacious suites is appointed with all the comforts of home. Start your day at the soothing water fountain in the atrium and relax on the rooftop deck enjoying the panoramic view of the Golden Gate Bridge.

neighborhood_overview:
Russian Hill is directly to the north (and slightly downhill) from Nob Hill, to the south (uphill) from Fisherman's Wharf, and to the west of the North Beach neighborhood. The Hill is bordered on its west side by parts of the neighborhoods of Cow Hollow and the Marina District.

At the northern foot of the hill is Ghirardelli Square, which sits on the waterfront of the San Francisco Bay, Aquatic Park, and Fisherman's Wharf, a popular tourist area. A trip down the winding turns of Lombard Street and across Columbus Avenue to the east leads to the neighborhood of North Beach. Down the hill to the west, past Van Ness Avenue, are Cow Hollow and the Marina districts.
